cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about Spoken Language Understanding (SLU), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). The proposed model, Collaborative Memory Network (CM-Net), is a deep learning model that uses memory networks to jointly model intent detection and slot filling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and speech processing. Additionally, the model uses deep learning techniques, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The model also involves information exchange among specific memories, local contexts, and global utterances, which suggests that cs.SD (Software Engineering) could be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the model uses memory networks, which are a type of neural network, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
